Looks like there might be a syntax error in your PL/SQL procedure definition. Here is the corrected syntax for your procedure to change the firm name:

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE change_firm_name (old_name VARCHAR2, new_name VARCHAR2) IS
BEGIN
    UPDATE Firms
    SET firm_name = new_name
    WHERE firm_name = old_name;

    COMMIT;

    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Firm name updated successfully.');
EXCEPTION
    WHEN OTHERS THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Error updating firm name: ' || SQLERRM);
END;
/
```

This procedure takes two input parameters old_name and new_name, and then updates the firm name in the Firms table where the old_name matches. Make sure the table name, column names, and data types match your actual schema. Afterwards, you can call this procedure to change the firm name.

Для включения еще одной процедуры в пакет, которая будет выводить компьютер с максимальной частотой, исключая компьютер, указанный в параметре, вам нужно сделать следующее:

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE PACKAGE ComputerPackage AS
    PROCEDURE change_firm_name(old_name VARCHAR2, new_name VARCHAR2);

    PROCEDURE find_max_frequency_computer(excluded_computer_id INT);
END ComputerPackage;
/

CREATE OR REPLACE PACKAGE BODY ComputerPackage AS
    PROCEDURE change_firm_name(old_name VARCHAR2, new_name VARCHAR2) IS
    BEGIN
        UPDATE Firms
        SET firm_name = new_name
        WHERE firm_name = old_name;

        COMMIT;

        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Firm name updated successfully.');
    EXCEPTION
        WHEN OTHERS THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Error updating firm name: ' || SQLERRM);
    END change_firm_name;

    PROCEDURE find_max_frequency_computer(excluded_computer_id INT) IS
        max_frequency NUMBER;
        computer_id NUMBER;
    BEGIN
        SELECT MAX(frequency), computer_id
        INTO max_frequency, computer_id
        FROM Computers
        WHERE computer_id <> excluded_computer_id;

        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Computer with max frequency: ' || computer_id || ', ' || max_frequency);
    EXCEPTION
        WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('No computer found with max frequency.');
        WHEN OTHERS THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Error finding computer with max frequency: ' || SQLERRM);
    END find_max_frequency_computer;
END ComputerPackage;
/
```

В этом примере, я добавил новую процедуру `find_max_frequency_computer` в пакет `ComputerPackage`. Эта процедура найдет компьютер с максимальной частотой, исключая компьютер, указанный в параметре `excluded_computer_id`. Вы можете вызвать эту процедуру, передавая идентификатор компьютера, который вы хотите исключить.

The error "ORA-01422: exact fetch returns more than requested number of rows" occurs when a SELECT INTO statement returns more than one row, while you are trying to fetch the result into a single variable. 

To address this issue, you can modify the procedure to handle the scenario where multiple rows are returned in the query. One approach is to use a cursor to fetch the results. Here is how you can update the procedure:

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE PACKAGE BODY ComputerPackage AS
    ...
    PROCEDURE find_max_frequency_computer(excluded_computer_id INT) IS
        max_frequency NUMBER;
        computer_id NUMBER;

        CURSOR c_max_frequency IS
          SELECT MAX(frequency) max_freq, computer_id
          FROM Computers
          WHERE computer_id <> excluded_computer_id
          GROUP BY computer_id
          ORDER BY MAX(frequency) DESC;
    BEGIN
        OPEN c_max_frequency;
        FETCH c_max_frequency INTO max_frequency, computer_id;

        IF c_max_frequency%NOTFOUND THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('No computer found with max frequency.');
        ELSE
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Computer with max frequency: ' || computer_id || ', ' || max_frequency);
        END IF;

        CLOSE c_max_frequency;
    EXCEPTION
        WHEN OTHERS THEN
            DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Error finding computer with max frequency: ' || SQLERRM);
    END find_max_frequency_computer;
END ComputerPackage;
/
```

In this updated version, a cursor `c_max_frequency` is used to fetch the maximum frequency and computer_id for all computers except the excluded one. The cursor fetches the results and orders them by frequency in descending order. Then, the fetch statement retrieves the first row from the cursor result set. If no rows are found, it will output an appropriate message.

